<configtype typenbr = "3">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "S8T40A1436022" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Camshaft and Tappet Inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "S8T40A1436021">Camshaft and Tappet Removal and Installation:J24B</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "S8T40A1436022001">
<title>
Cam Height
</title>
<ptxt>
Using a micrometer, measure cam height &#8220;a&#8221;. If measured height is out of standard values, replace camshaft.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Cam Height (IN)
</title>
<ptxt>
Standard: 47.023 &#8211; 47.183 mm (1.8513 &#8211; 1.8576 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 46.890 mm (1.8461 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<spec>
<title>
Cam Height (EX)
</title>
<ptxt>
Standard: 46.543 &#8211; 46.703 mm (1.8324 &#8211; 1.8387 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 46.420 mm (1.8276 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9T401142011.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "44.100mm" ver = "01" gw = "176" gh = "108"/>
</figure>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "S8T40A1436022002">
<title>
Camshaft Runout
</title>
<ptxt>
Set camshaft between two &#8220;V&#8221; blocks and measure its runout using a dial gauge.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If measured camshaft runout exceeds limit, replace camshaft.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Do not attempt to fix camshaft runout for reuse.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<spec>
<title>
Camshaft runout limit
</title>
<ptxt>
0.015 mm (0.00050 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9T401142012.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.745mm" ver = "01" gw = "136" gh = "124"/>
</figure>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "S8T40A1436022003">
<title>
Camshaft Journal
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Check camshaft journals and camshaft housings for pitting, scratches, wear or damage.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If any defective is found, replace camshaft or cylinder head with camshaft housings.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Do not attempt to fix malcondition of camshaft journal and camshaft housing for reuse.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
</item>
</list1>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9T401142013.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "38.103mm" ver = "01" gw = "88" gh = "91"/>
</figure>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "S8T40A1436022004">
<title>
Camshaft Journal Clearance
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean camshaft housings and camshaft journals.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove all tappets.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install camshafts and lower bearing half to cylinder head.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Place a piece of gauging plastic to full width of camshaft journal (parallel to camshaft).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install camshaft housing referring to steps 2) to 5) in &#8220;Installation&#8221; under 
<intxref refid = "S8T40A1436021">Camshaft and Tappet Removal and Installation:J24B</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Do not rotate camshaft while gauging plastic is installed.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove housings, and using scale (2) on gauging plastic envelop, measure gauging plastic (1) width at its widest point.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Camshaft journal clearance (intake side of camshaft housing No.1)
</title>
<ptxt>
Standard: 0.020 &#8211; 0.072 mm (0.00079 &#8211; 0.00244 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 0.10 mm (0.0039 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<spec>
<title>
Camshaft journal clearance (except intake side of camshaft housing No.1)
</title>
<ptxt>
Standard: 0.020 &#8211; 0.062 mm (0.00079 &#8211; 0.0024 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 0.095 mm (0.00374 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9T401142014.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.689mm" ver = "01" gw = "153" gh = "104"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>
If measured camshaft journal clearance exceeds limit, recheck camshaft journal clearance according to the following procedure.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Install camshaft upper bearing half and camshaft housings without camshafts to cylinder head.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Tighten camshaft housing bolts referring to Step 6) in &#8220;Installation&#8221; under 
<intxref refid = "S8T40A1436021">Camshaft and Tappet Removal and Installation:J24B</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
For intake camshaft journal No.1, measure journal outside diameter at positions shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If measured diameter is out of standard values, replace camshaft and recheck camshaft journal clearance.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If measured diameter is within standard values, replace camshaft bearings and recheck camshaft journal clearance.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
For all other camshaft journals, measure camshaft journal outside diameters and camshaft housing inside diameters.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If measured diameters are out of standard values, replace corresponding camshaft or cylinder head and camshaft housings.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Camshaft journal outside diameter
</title>
